      • expression

        public final FilterExpression.Clause expression()
                                         throws ParseException
        An expression is defined to be a queryTerm followed by zero or more query terms joined by either an AND or an OR. If two query terms are joined with AND then both conditions must be met. If two query terms are joined with an OR, then one of the two conditions must be met.
        Throws:
        ParseException
